01:15:05,864 --> 01:15:08,424
" On Christmas day, on Christmas day

731
01:15:08,499 --> 01:15:11,195
" I saw three ships come sailing by

732
01:15:11,269 --> 01:15:14,136
" On Christmas day in the morning

733
01:15:21,179 --> 01:15:24,876
It needs something... else.
What do you think, honey?

734
01:15:24,949 --> 01:15:27,884
- More bells?
- OK.

735
01:15:27,952 --> 01:15:30,978
Mom, do you really think
we should be having this party?

736
01:15:31,089 --> 01:15:33,887
Of course I think
we should be having this party.

737
01:15:33,958 --> 01:15:40,591
It's just what we need to calm things down...
and everything'll go back to normal.

738
01:15:42,433 --> 01:15:44,594
Do you have any more bells, honey?

739
01:17:36,614 --> 01:17:38,809
Now you've done it.

740
01:17:38,916 --> 01:17:41,407
It's just a scratch, Jim, really. It's OK.

741
01:17:41,486 --> 01:17:44,512
- Touch her again and I'll kill ya.
- It's no big deal.

742
01:17:44,622 --> 01:17:47,284
- Call a doctor. He skewered Kim.
- No!

743
01:17:47,358 --> 01:17:49,223
Stay away from her. I mean it!

744
01:17:49,293 --> 01:17:53,559
You can't touch anything without ruining it.
Why do you hang around here anyway?

745
01:17:53,664 --> 01:17:58,158
I want you to sit right down
and wait for me to bring you some ice.

746
01:17:58,269 --> 01:18:00,794
Stay right there. I'll be right back.

747
01:18:00,872 --> 01:18:06,310
" On Christmas day in the morning

748
01:18:06,844 --> 01:18:09,278
Get the hell outta here!

749
01:18:09,781 --> 01:18:12,341
Get the hell out! Go! Freak!

750
01:18:13,117 --> 01:18:15,278
Hey, Edward, where are you goin'?

751
01:18:23,127 --> 01:18:24,754
Where is he?

752
01:18:24,862 --> 01:18:27,558
- He tried to hurt you.
- He did not, and you know it.

753
01:18:27,665 --> 01:18:30,133
Are you nuts? I just saw him!

754
01:18:30,201 --> 01:18:35,104
Jim, I don't love you any more.
I just want you to go, OK? Just go!

755
01:18:35,873 --> 01:18:37,568
Are you serious?

756
01:18:37,675 --> 01:18:40,269
And lose you to that? He isn't even human.

757
01:18:40,344 --> 01:18:43,074
Just get out of here, OK? Just go!

758
01:18:51,089 --> 01:18:53,114
Dad, did you see where Edward went?

759
01:18:53,191 --> 01:18:55,716
I don't know. He just waltzed down the street.

760
01:18:55,793 --> 01:18:58,762
- We have to find him, Mom.
- Your father will find him.

761
01:18:58,830 --> 01:19:01,094
Go on in the house. I'll take care of it.

762
01:19:01,165 --> 01:19:03,224
I'll go find him.

763
01:19:20,551 --> 01:19:21,813
Edward!

764
01:19:21,919 --> 01:19:24,012
I'm calling the police!

765
01:20:11,869 --> 01:20:15,202
See all that blood, sweetie?
And it's just a little cut.

766
01:20:25,483 --> 01:20:27,974
Hello. I'm here to see the man with the hands.

767
01:20:32,123 --> 01:20:34,284
He's not here. Thank you.

768
01:20:35,293 --> 01:20:37,488
Oh, dear.

769
01:20:39,263 --> 01:20:41,595
Helen, did you actually see him?

770
01:20:41,666 --> 01:20:43,258
Yes! Look!

771
01:20:48,940 --> 01:20:51,101
I'm looking for the man with the scissors.

772
01:20:51,209 --> 01:20:54,610
- Thank God you're here.
- He went right down that way, sir.

773
01:20:54,679 --> 01:20:58,274
All right, calm down.
Go on home. We'll handle it.

774
01:20:58,349 --> 01:21:00,214
Just go home.

775
01:21:00,284 --> 01:21:04,220
- A demon. A demon.
- You gotta do somethin'!

776
01:21:11,829 --> 01:21:14,320
I'm sure your father'll find him soon.

777
01:21:15,032 --> 01:21:17,125
What time is it?

778
01:21:17,668 --> 01:21:21,627
It's almost 8:30. Great party, huh?

779
01:21:21,706 --> 01:21:23,765
Mom, where are they?

780
01:21:25,343 --> 01:21:28,335
- God, I hope he's OK.
- So do l, honey.

781
01:21:33,784 --> 01:21:37,584
You know, when I brought Edward
down here to live with us,

782
01:21:38,990 --> 01:21:41,652
I really didn't think things through.

783
01:21:42,693 --> 01:21:45,856
And I didn't think about
what could happen to him.

784
01:21:47,198 --> 01:21:50,690
Or to us. Or to the neighborhood.

785
01:21:53,070 --> 01:21:55,163
And now I think that maybe...

786
01:21:56,907 --> 01:21:58,966
it might be best if he goes...

787
01:22:00,511 --> 01:22:02,570
back up there.

788
01:22:03,347 --> 01:22:05,508
Because at least there he's safe.

789
01:22:07,885 --> 01:22:10,547
And we'd just go back to normal.

790
01:22:13,157 --> 01:22:16,615
I got halfway to the Whitmans'.
I didn't see him anywhere.

791
01:22:16,727 --> 01:22:18,957
Let's get in the car and go look for him.

792
01:22:19,030 --> 01:22:21,021
- Where's Kevin now?
- At Max's.

793
01:22:21,165 --> 01:22:22,962
Oh, for God's sakes!

794
01:22:23,034 --> 01:22:25,730
- Where do you think you're goin'?
- With you guys.

795
01:22:25,803 --> 01:22:30,240
- You stay here in case somebody shows up.
- We'll be right back, dear.

796
01:23:09,080 --> 01:23:11,207
Police!

797
01:23:47,985 --> 01:23:50,044
Edward?

798
01:23:52,890 --> 01:23:54,585
Are you OK?

799
01:23:55,926 --> 01:23:57,723
Yes. Are you OK?

800
01:24:01,932 --> 01:24:03,729
Where is everybody?

801
01:24:04,468 --> 01:24:06,527
Out looking for you.

802
01:24:12,610 --> 01:24:14,510
Hold me.

803
01:24:28,325 --> 01:24:29,724
I can't.

804
01:24:58,489 --> 01:25:02,892
I know it's a little early
for Christmas, Edward, but...

805
01:25:06,263 --> 01:25:08,356
I have a present for you.

806
01:27:06,784 --> 01:27:08,615
Forget holding her hand.

807
01:27:08,686 --> 01:27:11,246
Picture the damage he could do other places.

808
01:27:11,322 --> 01:27:13,449
Yeah. That's sick.

809
01:27:19,129 --> 01:27:22,030
I feel like I'm gonna pass out
or puke or something.

810
01:27:22,099 --> 01:27:24,624
Later. First, take me to her house.

811
01:27:24,702 --> 01:27:26,602
Come on. Don't make me drive.

812
01:27:26,670 --> 01:27:28,194
Just do it!

813
01:27:28,739 --> 01:27:30,730
Jesus. Maybe she was right about you.

814
01:27:30,841 --> 01:27:32,900
- Just drive!
- Relax!

815
01:27:37,247 --> 01:27:40,216
- See you tomorrow. Call me.
- All right.

816
01:27:58,469 --> 01:28:00,733
Have they caught him yet?

817
01:28:01,505 --> 01:28:04,736
- Who?
- Him! That cripple.

818
01:28:08,345 --> 01:28:10,313
Let me know when they do.

819
01:28:12,383 --> 01:28:14,510
Let us all know, OK?

820
01:28:15,552 --> 01:28:17,645
Like a good boy.

821
01:28:38,175 --> 01:28:39,665
Kevin.

822
01:28:44,682 --> 01:28:46,309
Are you OK?

823
01:28:46,383 --> 01:28:47,907
It's OK.

824
01:28:51,755 --> 01:28:53,916
- Edward, stop!
- I'm your friend.

825
01:28:58,529 --> 01:28:59,996
Help us!

826
01:29:02,566 --> 01:29:05,399
What are you doing? Get away from him!

827
01:29:14,011 --> 01:29:15,911
- Let go of me!
- What?

828
01:29:15,979 --> 01:29:17,776
Kevin!

829
01:29:24,455 --> 01:29:27,583
- Get away!
- Edward, come home!

830
01:29:59,289 --> 01:30:00,347
Run.

831
01:30:27,918 --> 01:30:31,479
Kevin's all right!
It was just the tiniest scratch!

832
01:30:31,622 --> 01:30:35,888
He's gone. Let's not bother him, all right?
Let's just leave him alone.

833
01:30:44,401 --> 01:30:46,460
Go on, run.

834
01:30:51,041 --> 01:30:53,805
- What happened? Is he dead?
- Did you get him?

835
01:30:54,444 --> 01:30:57,538
It's all over. Go on home.
There's nothing more to see.

836
01:30:57,681 --> 01:31:02,277
What happened out there?
I want to know! I want some answers!

837
01:31:02,352 --> 01:31:04,912
It is all over.

838
01:31:05,022 --> 01:31:07,081
Where is he?

839
01:31:08,892 --> 01:31:12,055
Get back here!
I wanna ask you something!

840
01:31:18,302 --> 01:31:20,532
Look at that! I don't believe this.

841
01:31:21,872 --> 01:31:23,863
They don't have him. I'm goin'.

842
01:31:23,941 --> 01:31:26,034
No! That's not a good idea.

843
01:32:31,441 --> 01:32:33,534
They're coming?

844
01:32:36,113 --> 01:32:38,104
Did I hurt Kevin?

845
01:32:38,181 --> 01:32:41,742
No, he's OK. Mostly he was just scared.

846
01:32:43,754 --> 01:32:46,382
Edward, I was so afraid.

847
01:32:47,024 --> 01:32:49,254
I thought you were dead.

848
01:32:57,000 --> 01:32:58,524
I didn't.

849
01:33:07,344 --> 01:33:08,834
No!

850
01:33:18,422 --> 01:33:20,083
No!

851
01:33:20,190 --> 01:33:22,181
Jim, stop!

852
01:33:39,109 --> 01:33:40,167
No!

853
01:33:43,780 --> 01:33:46,613
Stop it. Or I'll kill you myself.

854
01:33:58,595 --> 01:34:00,495
I said stay away from her!

855
01:35:00,657 --> 01:35:02,488
Goodbye.

856
01:35:13,770 --> 01:35:15,601
I love you.

857
01:36:03,820 --> 01:36:05,720
Is he in there?

858
01:36:07,924 --> 01:36:09,619
He's dead.

859
01:36:13,430 --> 01:36:15,591
The roof caved in on him.

860
01:36:16,666 --> 01:36:18,725
They killed each other.

861
01:36:21,571 --> 01:36:24,267
You can see for yourselves.

862
01:36:26,243 --> 01:36:27,972
See?

863
01:36:37,087 --> 01:36:39,180
I'm goin' home.

864
01:36:48,031 --> 01:36:50,090
Joyce...

865
01:37:07,284 --> 01:37:09,377
She never saw him again.

866
01:37:11,188 --> 01:37:13,281
Not after that night.

867
01:37:14,124 --> 01:37:16,217
How do you know?

868
01:37:22,999 --> 01:37:25,058
Because I was there.

869
01:37:25,702 --> 01:37:29,468
You could have gone up there.
You still could go.

870
01:37:30,807 --> 01:37:33,207
No, sweetheart.

871
01:37:33,276 --> 01:37:35,335
I'm an old woman now.

872
01:37:36,313 --> 01:37:39,111
I would rather him remember me
the way I was.

873
01:38:14,084 --> 01:38:16,143
How do you know he's still alive?

874
01:38:18,388 --> 01:38:20,549
I don't know.

875
01:38:20,657 --> 01:38:23,091
Not for sure, but...

876
01:38:23,660 --> 01:38:25,924
I believe he is.

877
01:38:35,305 --> 01:38:42,143
You see, before he came down here
it never snowed.

878
01:38:46,783 --> 01:38:50,378
And afterwards it did.

879
01:38:52,622 --> 01:38:57,559
If he weren't up there now,
I don't think it would be snowing.

880
01:39:00,163 --> 01:39:03,599
Sometimes you can still catch me
dancing in it.

